hahah, good on you for getting it back though
This has nothing to do with uber, but I got into a little reddit fight recently: <https://www.reddit.com/r/army/comments/3mnmcb/soldier_beaten_senseless_by_6_men_outside_plaza/cvglyb7>
I don't think I was being unreasonable, but maybe I'm wrong? I'm slingstone with the castle flare.

I think the original discussion of whether the bar owner should be at fault was lost almost immediately and that it then quickly degenerated. Other dude had some actual concern about it but was also trolling.
Otherwise both parties are probably right: you can almost always avoid that type of shit but sometimes you can't.
And I didn't read the original article but mostly that was relevant to the argument
The article was so sparse on facts while throwing around dogwhistle terms like gang and hoodlums that many readers filled in the blanks themselves (judging from the downvotes).
I just can't imagine getting into a barfight now, let alone at 37.
I had some one almost throw a punch at me recently but diffused it easily. I have also had friends randomly hit for being Asian so I can sympathize a bit with both sides of the argument
now, if only everyone had been packin' heat...
And could be assured that even if they shoot first, they and all they hold dear with burn in the retaliatory fires...
Oh right not talking about nation states

Started driving after the Steelers game. :disappointed:
Cancelled request. Someone is definitely smoking the gange out here.
Saw a big possum.
Zero requests in the last 90 minutes.
Read a neat article about attraction development in Disney parks, though.
Disappointing night; only 4 completed trips.
Down in the 60s here in Texas. It's lovely;  we're not far removed from triple-digit afternoons.
Another slow night. Maybe tests at Baylor next week?
So an SUV with a karaoke rig in the back is doing laps around the downtown bars.
This guy just walked by puking on the sidewalk. Didn't even slow down.
2 canceled requests so far. This may not be worth my time.

So I finally get a request: address is 8 miles out of town. I get there, park, text them my car marque and color, turn on the hazard lights, and wait. The guy calls to find out where I am. He put the destination address in as the pick-up location and gets kinda drunk-mad at me for not being there. I start driving to the actual location, but on the way he texts that he found a ride.
I decided it was not my night and came home. Sent uber and email to adjust the fare since I started the meter back at his house.
